definition.value: An amino disaccharide consisting of a beta-D-glucopyranose residue and a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A 6-deoxyaltrose that is beta-D-altrofuranose in which the hydroxy group at position 6 has been replaced by a hydrogen.
A glycosyl alditol consisting of alpha-D-glucopyranose and D-glucitol residues joined in sequence by a (1->6)-glycosidic bond.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of beta-D-glucopyranose and alpha-D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
